reviewText:
Dragon Age: Origins
Blood Age: Origins

If Darkspawn blood touches you, you die;

If Darkspawn blood touches you, you *could* become an obese tentacle monster with 100 boobs that gives birth to more darkspawn;
If you drink Darkspawn blood, you become invulnerable to it and you can defeat the Archdemon;
If you drink Darkspawn blood and kill the Archdemon, you die.
If Darkspawn drink your blood after you drank their blood, they become civilized, self-aware, beings;

If you are a mage, your blood is powerful;
If you are a mage and you use your blood in pursuit of power, you become a gross monster made of dead people;
If you steal research from a mage who will probably end up as a gross monster made of dead people you can make your blood extra powerful.
If you procure Dragon's blood, it can be used to make high quality equipment;

If you are a Dwarf, your blood will get you killed;
If you are a Human, your blood constitutes 7% of your body weight and transports Oxygen, Carbon Dioxide, Glucose, Amino Acids, Urea, Fatty Acids, Lactic Acid, Antibodies, Hormones, Coagulates and other nutrients and essential substances throughout your body while regulating and maintaining your body temperature and body Ph levels;
If you are an Elf, your blood can help locate invisible floating lanterns that can be used to find a magic mirror;
AND
If you are a ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ or an Orphaned Idiot-Savant, your blood means nothing.
